-- Jindal Saw to Begin Operating Waste-to-Energy Plant in New Delhi in 2011
-- Vandana Gombar
-- 2010-06-29T04:34:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/jindal-saw-to-begin-operating-waste-to-energy-plant-in-new-delhi-in-2011.html

          
          
                  June 29 (Bloomberg New Energy Finance) --  Jindal Saw Ltd. 
will begin operating its 16-megawatt waste-to-energy plant in
New Delhi in early 2011.  
 Timarpur-Okhla Municipal Solid Waste Management Co., set up
to manage the project, has a 25-year contract to obtain solid
waste from New Delhi city free of charge, according to a
statement from Jindal on June 26.  
 The plant has been registered with the United Nations to
earn carbon credits, said Indresh Batra, managing director of
Jindal Saw.  
